# JARVIS - Remote Dev Control

Control your laptop from your phone with AI assistance.

## Quick Start

### 1. Start Backend

```bash
python run.py
```

### 2. Expose with ngrok

```bash
ngrok http 8000
```

### 3. Run Mobile App

```bash
cd Frontend
npm install
npx expo start
```

## Features

| Feature          | Description                      |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------- |
| **Terminal**     | Execute shell commands remotely  |
| **Files**        | Browse and edit code files       |
| **AI Chat**      | GitHub Copilot / Ollama / OpenAI |
| **IDE**          | Open VS Code or Cursor           |
| **Git**          | Status, commit, push, pull       |
| **Multi-Laptop** | Switch between devices           |

## Project Structure

```
Jarvis/
├── src/jarvis/           # Backend (FastAPI)
│   ├── api/v1/           # API endpoints
│   │   └── mobile.py     # Main mobile API
│   ├── llm/providers/    # AI providers
│   └── devices/          # Multi-device support
├── Frontend/             # Mobile App (React Native)
│   ├── app/(tabs)/       # Tab screens
│   └── lib/              # API client & config
├── run.py                # Start server
└── remote_agent.py       # Remote laptop agent
```

## Configuration

Edit `Frontend/lib/config.ts`:

```typescript
backendUrl: "https://your-url.ngrok-free.dev";
```

## Build APK

```bash
cd Frontend
npm install -g eas-cli
eas login
eas build --platform android --profile preview --local
```

## AI Providers

| Provider           | Setup                        |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------- |
| **Ollama**         | Run locally: `ollama serve`  |
| **GitHub Copilot** | Add token in Settings        |
| **OpenAI**         | Set `OPENAI_API_KEY` env var |676
## Multi-Laptop

1. Run JARVIS + ngrok on each laptop
2. In app: Settings → Add Server
3. Switch between laptops anytime

## Environment Variables

```env
JARVIS_API_KEY=your-secret-key
JARVIS_LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
```

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Python 3.11, FastAPI, WebSockets
- **Frontend**: React Native, Expo, TypeScript
- **AI**: Ollama, GitHub Copilot, OpenAI

